  "texts": [
    "These may differ from the harmonized standards in Article 40, but Article 15 para 1a, with its wording, encourages a system of de-facto industry standards to exist equally besides the harmonized standards.",
    "Also, before the AI Act, robustness had an extensive tradition as a key aim in developing AI systems.",
    "In the Trustworthy AI Guidelines (High-Level Expert Group on AI 2019), systems are required to be \"lawful, ethical, and robust\" to be considered trustworthy.",
    "This document was already produced in 2019, and followed by a large number of policy initiatives undertaken by the European Commission (The European Comission 2018).",
    "Other actors, such as the OECD, have also picked up the notion of robustness, making it prominent in AI policy also outside and before the AI Act (OECD 2019)."
  ],
